regression: false
customer_impact: Untested branches and excluded entrypoints can regress without blocking delivery
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T20:26:50.702Z",codex-root,"Verification milestone: bun run test:coverage passes 1186 tests in 110 files with statements 100%, branches 100%, functions 100%, and lines 100%. Tests exercise production branches and failure semantics; no coverage exclusions or threshold escapes were added."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:13:54.759Z",codex-root,"Do not use c8/v8 ignore directives, exclude source entrypoints, lower thresholds, or create assertions that merely execute lines without checking behavior."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:13:55.600Z",codex-root,The current full run has 991 tests but only 95.44/84.75/96.30/96.11 coverage; test count is not a substitute for measured behavioral completeness.
  "2026-07-21T20:37:16.699Z",codex-root,"Honest 100% branch coverage improved production design: unreachable fallbacks, Commander option collisions, entrypoint side effects, non-Error catches, and sparse formatter shapes all became explicit and testable rather than hidden behind exclusions."
